# .mailmap — name/email canonicalization for git log, shortlog, blame,
# and GitHub's contributors graph.
#
# GitHub respects .mailmap when building the contributors panel, so any
# Co-authored-by trailer pointing at cursoragent gets folded back into
# the real human author. Non-destructive — no history rewrite required.
#
# Format reference:
#   <canonical-name> <canonical-email> <commit-name> <commit-email>
#
# If you want a full history rewrite that strips the Co-authored-by
# trailers entirely, see the "release flow" section in
# .agents/knowledgebase.md.

# Fold AI-agent co-authorship into the project owner. Both Cursor and
# GitHub Copilot CLI add a Co-authored-by trailer on commits authored
# through them; this remaps those identities to the human committer.
Haviduck <calleduck@gmail.com> Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Haviduck <calleduck@gmail.com> Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
